Key Match Events: Mitchell Marsh led Australia to a thumping win with a score of 201/7
Jos Buttler and Phil Salt made a fine start to the innings, but both were removed by Adam Zampa
Post-Match Reflections: Mitchell Marsh expressed his satisfaction with the team's performance
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was a Group B clash in the ICC Men's T20 World Cup at Bridgetown, Barbados
Others: England managed 165/6 in response to Australia's total
Chris Jordan got his 100th wicket of his T20 international career
